## (1)(b) ITU Function and Sectors

> Explain the function of the ITU (International Telecommunications Union) and its three sectors. *(4 marks)*

> *Learn more: [Standards Organizations](/wireless-communications/standards-organizations)*

The **ITU** is a United Nations agency that coordinates global telecommunications and radio spectrum.

**Three Sectors:**

| Sector | Name | Function |
|--------|------|----------|
| **ITU-R** | Radiocommunication | Manages radio spectrum and satellite orbits |
| **ITU-T** | Telecommunication Standardization | Develops technical standards (e.g., H.264, G.711) |
| **ITU-D** | Development | Helps developing countries build telecom infrastructure |

> The ITU also allocates country codes, manages international numbering plans, and coordinates spectrum to prevent interference between countries.

