## (1)(c) CSMA/CA Congestion Window

> Calculate the congestion window (CW) for the 3rd retransmission in the CSMA/CA protocol. The CW in the initial transmission is 63 slots. *(8 marks)*

> *Learn more: [CSMA/CA](/wireless-communications/wifi/csma-ca)*

In CSMA/CA, when a collision occurs, the congestion window **doubles** with each retransmission:

| Transmission | Calculation | CW |
|--------------|-------------|-----|
| Initial | - | 63 |
| 1st retransmission | 63 × 2 | 127 |
| 2nd retransmission | 127 × 2 | 255 |
| **3rd retransmission** | 255 × 2 | **511** |

The device then picks a random backoff value between 0 and CW (0-511), waits that many slot times, and tries again.

> **Answer: CW = 511 slots**
